hidden.m_name: Percent reduction of EMS transport to hospitals of enrolled CHP Clients

answers.textarea_31444284: The Apricot client management system is used to identify CHP clients, and to determine the duration of their enrollment in the program.  Based on information from this system, data regarding client contacts with the 911 system before and after their enrollment in the program is downloaded from the EMS Data Warehouse, and changes in utilization are calculated using Microsoft Excel.  This is currently done on an as-needed basis.
answers.textfield_31440655: Two Systems: Apricot (client management system) and EMS Data Warehouse
